<br>
Anything over 50 if they keep current implementation, will not help you in RvR vs. other players.  The effect on run speed and mob 'too close to hide' radius has yet to be determined over spec 50, but that's not the point of this post.<br>
<br>
Maybe I worded it wrong, but if you have stealth at or above the seeker's level and you are stealthed, they can see you within the minimum detection range.  Points in stealth above their level do not change this minimum detection range in all tests that I performed.<br>
<br>
Hence, extrapolate to the &quot;everyone is level 50 scenario&quot; .. with you being stealthed with an assumed 50 spec with items, everyone can see you within the minimum detection range.<br>
<br>
There are still client/datastream issues (like how data sent that 'pops' a stealthed character into transparent mode, but first renders them fully visible for a split-second, is only sent every 3ish seconds, so moving at a full run you may never see a stealthed character even if you are in range to see them, unless you pause long enough for the 3 second data to get sent).  I've mentioned those issues to the devs as well, but my first impression is that those aren't as easy to fix as simply making detect hidden classes have an extended minimum detection radius.  Although they are still valid concerns that do affect the skill. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse>The Safehouse</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19>Main Hall</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.thesafehouse.org">The Safehouse website</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.guildboss.com"><img
